Popular free Command Combinations

Human-readable output (Most common):
free -h
Displays memory in Gigabytes (Gi) or Megabytes (Mi), making it much easier to read.
Continuous monitoring:
free -s 2

Updates the memory statistics every 2 seconds. Press Ctrl+C to stop it.
Monitor for a specific number of times:
free -s 2 -c 5

Updates every 2 seconds, but stops automatically after 5 updates.
Show Total memory (including swap):
free -h -t

Adds a "Total" row at the bottom that summarizes your physical memory and swap.
View in Gigabytes:
free -g

Useful if you want to see large memory values in a cleaner, whole-number format (GB).
Quick Summary of Options
Option	Description
-h	Human-readable (auto-scales to B, K, M, G).
-m	Display in Megabytes (MiB).
-g	Display in Gigabytes (GiB).
-s [sec]	Repeat output every specified number of seconds.
-c [count]	Repeat output a specific number of times.
-t	Show the total row.
-w	Wide output mode (prevents text from wrapping on smaller screens).
